 Guy|William Augustus Guy]], ''The Numerical Method and its Application to the Science and Art of Medicine''<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1136/bmj.s4-1.188.593 |pmid=20743755 |pmc=2252920 |title=Croonian Lectures on the Numerical Method, and its Application to the Science and Art of Medicine |year=1860 |last1=Guy |first1=W. A. |journal=BMJ |volume=s4-1 |pages=593\u2013597 |issue=188}}</ref>\n*1859 [[William Brinton]], ''On Intestinal Obstruction''<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(02)45700-5 |title=Croonian Lectures, ON INTESTINAL OBSTRUCTION |year=1859 |journal=The Lancet |volume=73 |issue=1864 |pages=501\u2013504}}</ref>\n*1858 [[Alexander John Sutherland]], ''On the Pathology, Morbid Anatomy, and Treatment of Insanity'' <ref>{{cite journal|doi= 10.1192/bjp.7.36.161|title=Croonian Lectures. On the Pathology, Morbid Anatomy, and Treatment of Insanity, delivered at the Royal College of Physicians, London, 1858|journal=  Journal of Mental Science|volume=7|issue=36|year=1861|pages=161\u2013179|last1=Sutherland|first1=Alex. John}}</ref>\n*1857\n*1856 [[G. Owen Rees]], ''On Calculous Disease and its Consequences''<ref>{{cite journal|title= On Calculous Disease and its Consequences|journal=Association Medical Journal|volume=4|issue=198|pages=889\u2013891|year=1856|jstor=25497594}}</ref>\n*1855 [[Patrick Black]]<ref name=\"radcliffe-oxford.com\">{{cite web|url = http://www.radcliffe-oxford.com/books/samplechapter/2366/12-Merchant_Navy_Pt2-Ch12-pp-6a3ffd00rdz.pdf|title = Administrators, Physicians and Surgeons who served during the ship era|accessdate = 12 August 2010|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110715144507/http://www.radcliffe-oxford.com/books/samplechapter/2366/12-Merchant_Navy_Pt2-Ch12-pp-6a3ffd00rdz.pdf|archive-date = 15 July 2011|url-status = dead}}</ref>\n*1854 [[Charles West (physician)|Charles West]], ''Pathological Importance of Ulceration of the Os Uteri''\n*1853 [[Thomas Mayo (physician)|Thomas Mayo]], ''Medical Testimony and Evidence in 