opulated places established in 1574]]\n[[Category:Populated places on Manila Bay]]\n[[Category:Populated places on the Pasig River]]\n[[Category:Port cities and towns in the Philippines]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Capital and chief port of the Philippines}}\n{{redirect2|Maynila|Maynilad|the TV series|Maynila (TV series)|related water companies|Maynilad Water Services|and|Manila Water}}\n{{About|the capital city of the Philippines|the region|Metro Manila|other uses}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name = Manila\n| native_name = ''Maynil\u00e0''\n| native_name_lang = fil\n| official_name = ''Lungsod ng Maynil\u00e0''<br /><small>(City of Manila)</small> <!-- as per seal -->\n| settlement_type = [[Capital of the Philippines|Capital]] and [[Cities of the Philippines|Highly Urbanized City]]\n| image_skyline = {{Photomontage\n| photo1a = Big Manila.jpg\n| photo2b = Manila City Hall Clock Tower View from Intramuros Wall.jpg\n| photo2a = Fort Santiaigo in Intramuros.jpg\n| photo4a = Rizal Monument at Dusk.jpg\n| photo4b = Allan Jay Quesada- Quiapo Church DSC 0065 The Minor Basilica of the Black Nazarene or Quiapo Church, Manila.JPG\n| photo5a = Malaca\u00f1ang Palace (Cropped).jpg\n| size = 250\n| spacing = 2\n| position = center\n| color = transparent\n| border = 0\n}}\n| image_caption = Clockwise from top: Manila Bay skyline, [[Fort Santiago]], [[Quiapo Church]], [[Malaca\u00f1an Palace]], [[Rizal Monument]], [[Manila City Hall]]\n| image_flag = {{PH wikidata|image_flag}}\n| flag_size = 120x80px\n| image_seal = Ph seal ncr manila.svg\n| seal_size = 100x80px\n| seal_link = Coat of arms of Manila\n| image_shield = \n| nickname = Pearl of the Orient<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1945/02/05/archives/pearl-of-orient-stripped-of-food-manila-before-pearl-harbor-had.html|title= 'Pearl of Orient' Stripped of Food; Manila, Before Pearl Harbor, Had Been Prosperous\u2014Its Harbor One, of Best Focus for Two Attacks Osme\u00f1a Succe